#### What do I want to measure?

To test whether our hands are equal or equivalent (<htcite0>), we need to define what we will compare. For example, we can list three possible measurements:
- Number of fingers;
- Size of fingers;
- Size of the hand.

After we define what will be compared, we can estimate the desired outcome. When we say our two hands are equal, it means there are no differences between them, that the list of differences is empty; that is, equal to zero (<htcite1>).
